OL,3,C'He wasn't accountable to anyone':
OL,4,CFailures to discipline Neil Foden
OL,5,Crevealed
OL,7,FNeil Foden, on behalf of the school,
OL,8,Fdenied all allegations made against
OL,9,Fthe school at the time.
OL,11,FMrs Wilson believes the governing body
OL,12,Fat Ysgol Friars and Gwynedd Council
OL,13,Fshould have dismissed Foden following
OL,14,Fthe tribunal, and she claims that the
OL,15,Fchair of Governors, Essi Ahari, failed
OL,16,Fto ensure that Neil Foden faced any
OL,17,Fconsequence for his behaviour.
