OL,3,C'He wasn't accountable to anyone':
OL,4,CFailures to discipline Neil Foden
OL,5,Crevealed
OL,7,FThe member of staff who wishes to
OL,8,Fremain anonymous told Y Byd ar Bedwar
OL,9,Fthat the governing body had received a
OL,10,FFreedom of Information request asking
OL,11,Fto see any discussions surrounding the
OL,12,Foutcomes of employment tribunals
OL,13,Fbetween 2015 and 2023, including Simon
OL,14,FWilson's case.
OL,16,FThese would include any discussions
OL,17,Fsurrounding any possible disciplinary
OL,18,Factions taken against Neil Foden. But
OL,19,Fin their response the governors
OL,20,Frefused to release any of the
OL,21,Fdiscussions regarding the cases.
