OL,3,C'He wasn't accountable to anyone':
OL,4,CFailures to discipline Neil Foden
OL,5,Crevealed
OL,7,FLittle more than a week after Foden
OL,8,Fwas found guilty, Essi Ahari, the
OL,9,Fchair of the governing body at Ysgol
OL,10,FFriars, and the deputy chair, stepped
OL,11,Fdown.
OL,13,FIn his resignation letter, which he
OL,14,Fhas shared with the programme, Mr
OL,15,FAhari describes the verdict against
OL,16,FNeil Foden as a "milestone".
OL,18,FHe added that he and the deputy chair
OL,19,Fhad been discussing "the best outcome
OL,20,Ffor Friars" and "the board and us as
OL,21,Findividuals".
